div.p:
The entrance into this State,
Adoleſcence. what is it elſe but the deſtruction of Infancy? What is Manhood, but the death of Youth? What is the riſing of to morrow, but the ſetting of this day? If therefore we rightly conſider the thing, when Men deſire a change of their Condition, they deſire Death, and judge their preſent State unhappy;

they are diſcontented with their preſent Condition, and therefore cannot be happy in it.
